            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Fy2F8nFTPcXnfAAEzFDMDg\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Let me break down what makes these keywords effective for your scheduling tool:\\n\\n**1. Search Intent Alignment**\\nYour keywords match what people are *actively searching for* when they have a scheduling problem. Someone typing \\\"meeting scheduler for remote teams\\\" is already thinking about your solution—they're not just browsing. This is high-intent traffic.\\n\\n**2. Specificity Over Breadth**\\nNotice we avoided generic terms like just \\\"scheduling\\\" or \\\"calendar.\\\" Instead, we combined:\\n- **Who** (remote teams, distributed companies)\\n- **What** (meeting scheduler, calendar tool)\\n- **Problem** (time zones, coordination)\\n\\nThis specificity means fewer irrelevant clicks and lower costs. A generic keyword might attract someone looking for personal calendar apps—a waste of your budget.\\n\\n**3. Problem-Focused Language**\\nKeywords like \\\"eliminate scheduling back and forth\\\" and \\\"automatic scheduling across time zones\\\" speak directly to your audience's pain points. When someone searches these phrases, they're frustrated with their current process—perfect timing for your solution.\\n\\n**4. Commercial Intent**\\nWords like \\\"scheduler,\\\" \\\"software,\\\" \\\"tool,\\\" and \\\"planner\\\" signal buying intent. People using these terms are looking for a solution to purchase or try, not just learning about scheduling in general.\\n\\n**5. Competitive Positioning**\\nKeywords like \\\"automatic scheduling across time zones\\\" differentiate you. They highlight what makes your tool unique compared to generic calendar apps.\\n\\n**The Bottom Line:** Effective keywords are the bridge between what your audience is searching for and what you're offering. They should be specific enough to attract the right people, but broad enough to capture real search volume.\\n\\nWhich of these keywords resonate most with your target audience? Any you'd like to adjust?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2937,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":385,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
